This paper is primarily focused on human-robot collaboration, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as Interaction Probabilistic Movement Primitives (ProMPs) and Electromyography (EMG) signals, which are relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.HC.
